						               													<description>In Harry Potter Championship Quidditch players take on the role of either Harry Potter or Draco Malfoy in a high-energy 1-on-1 version of author J.K. Rowling's magical sport. &amp;#10;Each player must fire small red balls - quaffles - through rotating hoops in the center of the playing field. Each successful shot is worth ten points, but also more often than not gives the quaffle to your opponent. With eight quaffles flying back and forth, though, there's plenty to go around!&amp;#10;At a random point in the contest, the game will launch a gold ping-pong-esque ball - the Golden Snitch -  into the air. Whichever player catches the ball is awarded 150 points, and the game ends.&amp;#10;The game, which runs on two C batteries, provides sound effects during the game and also keeps track of the score, which can get into the thousands.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
